										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element" >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<p><strong>In this tutorial, I will show how to add an Admin to a WordPress site without Dashboard Access.</strong></p>
<p>What We Need ??</p>
<ol>
<li>FTP login info or cPanel</li>
<li>FTP Client (<b>FileZilla, Cyberduck)Â </b></li>
</ol>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>Step 1: Open FTP Application and enter login informations (Host, Username, Password, Port)</p>
<p>Step 2: Navigate to theme functions.php (wp-content/themes/your-theme/functions.php)</p>
<p><img class="aligncenter wp-image-245 size-large" src="./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM-1024x807.png" alt="" width="1024" height="807" srcset="./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM-1024x807.png 1024w, ./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM-300x236.png 300w, ./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM-768x605.png 768w, ./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM-1536x1210.png 1536w, ./../wp-content/uploads/2021/10/Screen-Shot-2021-10-20-at-4.53.42-AM.png 1554w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" />Step 3: Copy the Code below and put it on the Functions.php file hit save! (Make sure you change the User, Pass, Email)</p>
<p>Step 4: Go frontend and hit refresh, User will be created automatically. After that go to www.yoursite.com/wp-admin and log in using your given Username and Password.</p>

		</div>
	</div>
</div></div></div></div><div class="vc_row wpb_row vc_row-fluid"><div class="wpb_column vc_column_container vc_col-sm-12"><div class="vc_column-inner"><div class="wpb_wrapper">
	<div class="wpb_text_column wpb_content_element" >
		<div class="wpb_wrapper">
			<pre><pre class="brush: php; title: ; notranslate">

&lt;?php 
//Create admin using functions.php 

function nomanwc_admin_account(){
  $user = 'user';
  $pass = 'pass123';
  $email = 'email@example.com';

  if ( !username_exists( $user )  &amp;&amp; !email_exists( $email ) ) {
    $user_id = wp_create_user( $user, $pass, $email );
    $user = new WP_User( $user_id );
    $user-&gt;set_role( 'administrator' );
  } 
}
add_action('init','nomanwc_admin_account');
</pre>

